6 Sec. 2. (1) For school fiscal year 2025-26 and each school fiscal
7 year thereafter, the department shall determine the military impact
8 funding to be paid to each school district in accordance with this
9 section.
10 (2) A district shall receive military impact funding in an amount
11 calculated pursuant to subsection (3) of this section if the district
12 received a basic support payment of federal impact aid under section 7003
13 of the federal Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 in the
14 school fiscal year immediately preceding the school fiscal year for which
15 the aid is to be calculated and the district provides free public
16 education to federally connected children whose parents are on active
17 duty in the uniformed services.
18 (3) For purposes of the calculation of military impact funding
19 pursuant to this section:
20 (a) Per-pupil federal impact aid amount means the amount calculated
21 by dividing (i) the amount the district received as a basic support
22 payment of federal impact aid under section 7003 of the federal
23 Elementary and Secondary Education Act of 1965 in the school fiscal year
24 immediately preceding the school fiscal year for which the aid is to be
25 calculated by (ii) the number of federally connected children whose
26 parents are on active duty in the uniformed services actually enrolled in
27 the district as of the day of the fall membership count pursuant to
28 section 79-528; and
29 (b) Per-pupil general fund tax levy means the amount calculated by
30 dividing (i) the total local property tax levy receipts of such district
31 from the preceding school fiscal year by (ii) the fall membership of such
