4 (4)(a) The amount of military impact funding provided to a district
5 shall be calculated by (i) subtracting the per-pupil federal impact aid
6 from the per-pupil general fund tax levy and (ii) multiplying the amount
7 calculated in subdivision (a)(i) of this subsection by the number of
8 federally connected children whose parents are on active duty in the
9 uniformed services actually enrolled in the district as of the day of the
10 fall membership count pursuant to section 79-528.
11 (b) A district's military impact funding shall be zero if the amount
12 calculated pursuant to subdivision (4)(a)(i) produces a negative result.
